docs.abstract: Apple had said its HomePod speaker, a response to Amazon’s Echo, would debut this year. Now it won’t be released till early next year.
docs.snippet: Apple had said its HomePod speaker, a response to Amazon’s Echo, would debut this year. Now it won’t be released till early next year.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Apple is putting the brakes on the arrival this year of HomePod, its much-ballyhooed rival to Amazon’s Echo smart speaker.

headline.main: Apple Postpones Release of HomePod Speaker
headline.print_headline: Apple Says  HomePod Isn’t Ready  For Release

docs.abstract: Two new books offer startlingly different conclusions on Silicon Valley’s influence on our economy, culture and politics.
docs.snippet: Two new books offer startlingly different conclusions on Silicon Valley’s influence on our economy, culture and politics.
docs.lead_paragraph: The pervasive influence of Silicon Valley on our economy, culture and politics is a subject worthy of close study. Two important new books released this week offer startlingly different approaches and conclusions on these complex issues. The contrasting epigraphs that begin the works perfectly reflect their respective perspectives.

headline.main: Review: Two Contrasting Views of Silicon Valley’s Influence

docs.abstract: Your smartphone is not deliberately losing speed just because your phone maker has a new gadget for sale. For devices that do slow down, here are some fixes.

docs.abstract: Many participants in a recent study failed to recreate famous logos from brands like Apple and Starbucks. But some experts say that shouldn’t worry companies.

docs.abstract: It’s planning to end net neutrality while opposing the Time Warner and AT&T merger. This doesn’t make sense.

docs.lead_paragraph: Peter Thiel, Facebook’s first outside investor, once wrote: “Competition is for losers. If you want to create and capture lasting value, look to build a monopoly.” Executives at Facebook, Google and Amazon seem to have taken his blunt advice.

headline.main: The Trump Administration’s Incoherent Stance on Competition

docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — After years of trying unsuccessfully to build a social network to rival Facebook, Google finally got something out of all of its failures: cover.
